pageContext.description: Condition perfect; point fairly sharp, edges very sharp. Lozenge shaped loops. Flared-out mouth to socket, above which are give close-set grooves, from which springs a pattern of chevrons filled in with hatching. Slight ribs on blades of wings, running parallel to the edges.
pageContext.patina: One side has its original dark brown patina; the other has been cleaned and is highly burnished.
pageContext.associations: Flint flakes and arrowheads, pierced bones, etc.
pageContext.site: England,Yorkshire N.R.,Bainbridge,N. side of semer Water, on the site of Cake dwelling. Found lying on impact of blue clay, which has been [dennled?] of its covering of mud.
pageContext.toSearch: Bainbridge, Leyburn, North Yorkshire Dl8, UK
pageContext.remarks: Cf spearhead from Clifton Grove, Notts, of same [same?] and much the same decoration.
